<p><b>Niklas Luhmann</b> (<span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1927-12-08"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="12-08"><a href="/wiki/December_8" title="December 8">December 8</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1927" title="1927">1927</a></span> - <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1998-11-06"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="11-06"><a href="/wiki/November_6" title="November 6">November 6</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1998" title="1998">1998</a></span>) was a <a href="/wiki/Germany" title="Germany">German</a> <a href="/wiki/Sociologist" title="Sociologist" class="mw-redirect">sociologist</a>, administration expert, and a prominent thinker in sociological <a href="/wiki/Systems_theory" title="Systems theory">systems theory</a>.</p>
